So data collection and data analysis is going to be one of the the keys to success in this project.
This week we received the equipment and protocol from Fifi, downloaded the application from MaddCog and took 1 hour to run the test.
The test may look easy, but it actually much harder than I expected.
Because I only take one ten-minute section and felt tired anyhow.
But still, I recon this is a right and fast way in capturing testers mental fatigue through EEG and HRV.
As their is no gold standard method of measuring mental fatigue, it is not something we can 'measure'.
Our model aims to predict mental fatigue, and we base the prediction on time on task during this 1 hour test.
However, before signing the NDA form, we still not have the access to reading the existing 27 tests data collecting by MaddCog.
Thus, we still can not decide what types of visualization we are going to use, e. g.  correlation matrix, clustering, pie charts, and time series analysis.
Hopefully we can get the data as soon as possible and play with data for learning.
Before writing the proposal, I did some research for mental fatigue.

Although this is not relevant to how to predict mental fatigue, I discovered that there is one paragraph in an interesting book(in mandarin) which is telling us " A Psychology Professor from Chicago, RoniÂ Jacobson, tells people that the most efficient way to releaseÂ mental fatigue is trying to let yourself in a lighter state of mind.

You have to loosen up your eye extrinsic muscles because eye sight is one of the most important and most energy consuming which occupied around 1/4 energy consumption throughout nervous system in our body.
Therefore, to loosen up your tight eye muscles is the most effective way releasing fatigue. "
Furthermore, as far as I know there is a product called steam eye mask, if the client could license this technology to.
gaming headset brands with eye mask which would be a most amazing invention.
Aside from that, I found that Fifi has published some articles on Medium Â which gave us an insight into the problems of mental fatigue.
We are not only in learning how to predict a model but also in learning how the prediction can be turned into real time actionable feedback.
The true value is telling the player they were likely to make a mistake before they even made it.
Thus, this might allow them to refocus and hopefully avoid the mistake.
